most_active_tickets.title: VScode extension continuously requesting installation, never installs unable to load extension
Authentication Loop and 500 Internal Server Error on Sign In

common_issues.title: Users unable to sign in to Pieces OS across platforms
common_issues.description: Multiple users report issues signing into Pieces OS on desktop and VS Code extension.  Symptoms include continuous installation requests for the VS Code extension, authentication loops, and 500 internal server errors.  Browser extensions seem less affected.  Logs reveal issues with the /os/sign_in endpoint.  Pro users also report not accessing pro features despite being logged in.

related_issues.title: Authentication Loop and 500 Internal Server Error on Sign In
related_issues.text:
Authentication Loop and 500 Internal Server Error on Sign In
### Checked for Existing Issues?

- [x] Yes, I have checked existing issues and cannot find one related to this.

### Software

Desktop Application

### Operating System / Platform

macOS

### Your Pieces OS Version

12.2.1

### Early Access Program

- [ ] Yes, this is related to an Early Access Program feature.

### Kindly describe the bug and include as much detail as possible on what you were doing so we can reproduce the bug.

Hello Pieces Team,

I'm unable to log in to my Pieces OS account. When I click the "Sign In" button, my browser opens and then immediately redirects me to an authentication-error page. This creates an infinite loop, preventing me from accessing the application.

The log files indicate that a 500 Internal Server Error is occurring when the application makes a POST request to the /os/sign_in endpoint.

Steps to Reproduce
Open the Pieces OS application.

Click on the "Sign In" button.

The browser opens to the authentication page.

It immediately fails and redirects to the error URL: https://pieces.app/authentication-error?sentry_id=...

Expected Behavior
I expect to be successfully authenticated and logged into the Pieces OS application.

Actual Behavior
An infinite authentication loop occurs, and I cannot log in. The application logs show a clear HTTP 500 error during the sign-in attempt.

System Information
OS: Windows

Pieces OS Version: 12.2.1 (from logs)
